{"name":"Catacomb Saint","type":"class","img":"modules/morkborg-3p/images/tokens/catacomb-saint.png","data":{"abilities":"<p>Begins with 3d6x10s and d4 Omens. HP: Toughness + d6</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Literally a skeleton, roll 3d6 for Presence and Agility, 3d6-2 for Strength and Toughness. Roll a d8 for weapon, d2+2 armor. You start with a random sacred scroll, and can use sacred scrolls in medium or heavy armor. Undead, you do not eat, breath, sleep, or have any other functions that the living would have. You cannot become infected, but only resting can heal you, as you focus on the sacred rites that keep you together.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You were charged with the care of one sacred relic:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>SAINT BRITA&rsquo;S PURGING SWORD</li>\n<li>BASILISK MITER</li>\n<li>HOLIEST WATER</li>\n<li>SAINT KARL&rsquo;S CHAPLET OF EVERLASTING LIFE</li>\n<li>CRUCIFIX OF THE DEAD</li>\n<li>THE ARM OF SAINT JOHAN</li>\n<li>WERNA&rsquo;S SHIELD OF FAITH</li>\n<li>SAINT PELLE&rsquo;S APOCRYPHA</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Who were you? (d6)</p>\n<ol>\n<li>A reformer, you have a strange notion of church doctrine, near incompatible with the current clergy.</li>\n<li>A warrior, you brought glory in the church&rsquo;s name.</li>\n<li>A martyr, the fools wouldn&rsquo;t listen, no matter how much you warned them. They killed you, but they died shortly after.</li>\n<li>A convert, you saw the Truth of the church late in life. Your story is still told as proof of faith convincing even the most stubborn to convert.</li>\n<li>A well-loved member of the clergy, the church has forgotten you.</li>\n<li>You stole a relic, but died shortly after, cursed to guard it for eternity.</li>\n</ol>","armorTableDie":"1d2+2","description":"Anointed in ages past, these richly-adorned skeletons watch over the holy resting places and sacred relics of the One True Faith. Many have been branded apostates for irreconcilable differences in interpretation of scripture with current clergy, and more have been driven from their holy grounds, forced to wander the world.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingItems":"morkborg-3p.class-catacomb-saint,Undead\nmorkborg-3p.class-catacomb-saint,Sacred Caster","startingPresence":"3d6","startingRolls":"morkborg-3p.rolls-catacomb-saint,Who were you?,1\nmorkborg-3p.rolls-catacomb-saint,Sacred Relics,1\nmorkborg.random-tables,Sacred Scrolls,1","startingSilver":"3d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6-2","weaponTableDie":"1d8"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"7liZlUNfTdrLYETW":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.V6KdNxxeau3Tyvw7"}},"_id":"ktYfH0f5gY4cCHMl"}
